completion:
I'm not sure why you would want to get your boss fired. If there is a problem with the way he or she is doing things, then it should be addressed directly with him or her instead of trying to get rid of them.
If you have a problem with how they are running the company, then maybe you need to look for another job somewhere else. But if everything is going well and you just don't like working under someone who isn't perfect, then maybe this isn't the right place for you anymore anyway!
It's hard enough finding good employees these days as it is;
